ball.tools.javadoc

Interface Doclet


  • public interface Doclet
    Doclet "interface." Doclets are not actually part of a class hierarchy. The methods described here are static in the implementations. This interface is provided to document the methods and to use as a possible basis for creating Proxy-based solutions. The standard OpenJDK DocumentationTool dispatches to Standard which in-turn dispatches to HtmlDoclet.
    Version:
    $Revision: 5285 $
    Author:
    Allen D. Ball

      • validOptions

        boolean validOptions(String[][] options,
                     DocErrorReporter reporter)
        Check options have correct arguments. The Standard supplies an instance of com.sun.tools.javadoc.Messager Doclet for DocErrorReporter.
        Parameters:
        options - The options and their arguments.
        reporter - The DocErrorReporter.
        Returns:
        true if the options are valid; false otherwise.

      • optionLength

        int optionLength(String option)
        Check for Doclet added options. E.g., "-d docs" should return 2.
        Parameters:
        option - The option to check.
        Returns:
        Number of arguments required to specify; 0 means the option is unknown and a negative value indicates an error.

      • start

        boolean start(RootDoc root)
        Starting point for document generation. The Standard supplies an instance of com.sun.tools.javadoc.RootDocImpl Doclet for RootDoc.
        Parameters:
        root - The RootDoc.
        Returns:
        true on success; false otherwise.
